What happens when you type https://www.google.com in your browser and press Enter?

--------------------------------------------------

1. DNS REQUEST
The browser first asks DNS to translate www.google.com into an IP address.

--------------------------------------------------

2. TCP CONNECTION
The browser connects to the server using TCP/IP and establishes a reliable connection (3-way handshake).

--------------------------------------------------

3. FIREWALL
Firewalls check the request and block unsafe or unwanted traffic before it reaches the servers.

--------------------------------------------------

4. HTTPS / SSL
The browser and server establish a secure encrypted connection using SSL/TLS so data is protected.

--------------------------------------------------

5. LOAD BALANCER
A load balancer receives the request and sends it to one available server to distribute traffic evenly.

--------------------------------------------------

6. WEB SERVER
The web server (like Nginx) receives the request:
- Serves static files directly
- Sends dynamic requests to the application server

--------------------------------------------------

7. APPLICATION SERVER
The application server runs the website logic and processes the request.

--------------------------------------------------

8. DATABASE
If needed, the application server asks the database for data and receives a response.

--------------------------------------------------

9. RESPONSE
The response goes back:
Database → Application Server → Web Server → Browser

The browser then displays the page.